5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 169, L.D. 388, “An Act to Provide
10 Access to Quality Family Child Care for Military Personnel by Exempting Certain Military
11 Child Care Providers from State Licensing Requirements”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §8301-A, sub-§10 is enacted to read:
15 10. Exemption from duplicative licensure. Notwithstanding any provision of this
16 chapter to the contrary, a child care facility or family child care provider on a military
17 installation or a facility licensed or certified as a family child care provider by the United
18 States Department of Defense or by the United States Coast Guard that provides care only
19 for children of parents or guardians who are active duty military members is exempt from
20 the requirements of this chapter.'
21 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
22 number to read consecutively.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This amendment clarifies that a child care facility or family child care provider that is
2255 licensed or certified by the United States Department of Defense or the United States Coast
2266 Guard and provides care only for children of parents or guardians who are active duty
2277 military members is exempt from state licensing requirements.
